03:20.080 --> 03:22.550
[gasping]

03:22.620 --> 03:25.450
- Taylor?

03:25.460 --> 03:27.490
- TAYLOR!
- Move! Move, move, move, move!

03:30.190 --> 03:32.190
- Taylor!

03:32.260 --> 03:34.600
Get out of the way!
Get out of the way!

03:38.400 --> 03:40.940
[theme music]

03:41.000 --> 03:42.840
♪♪♪

03:48.080 --> 03:50.010
[distant siren blaring]

03:50.010 --> 03:52.550
[tense music]

03:52.620 --> 03:54.550
♪♪♪

04:00.620 --> 04:02.590
[streetcar bell dinging]

04:04.790 --> 04:07.030
- Seizures,
uncontrollable twitching,

04:07.100 --> 04:09.060
loss of motor function.
There is nothing tying

04:09.130 --> 04:11.000
these symptoms to either...

04:11.070 --> 04:14.770
Sodium Chloride or...
what is it again?

04:14.840 --> 04:16.500
- Polysorbate.
- Polysorbate!

04:16.570 --> 04:19.170
- Why won't that stay in my head?
- Just take a breath, Counselor.

04:19.240 --> 04:21.209
[man sighing]
- I can't lose this injunction.

04:21.279 --> 04:23.540
- We're not going to.
- I should've had this all

04:23.610 --> 04:25.380
wrapped up last week.
Made that stupid mistake

04:25.450 --> 04:27.950
- on the signed affidavit.
- Hey! The key

04:28.020 --> 04:30.050
to winning law?
No short term memory.

04:30.120 --> 04:32.020
- That's easy for you
to say. You have

04:32.090 --> 04:34.060
a nearly photographic one.

04:34.120 --> 04:36.160
[sighing]

04:36.230 --> 04:38.190
- OK. Let's go over it again.

04:38.260 --> 04:41.530
You'll talk about
symptoms, chemicals.

04:41.600 --> 04:43.730
I'll pepper in some data

04:43.800 --> 04:45.670
about proving cause,
and then I'll set you up

04:45.740 --> 04:48.300
for the big spike.

04:50.270 --> 04:52.670
- What?
- Thank you...

04:52.740 --> 04:55.680
for, you know, stepping up,
helping me out.

04:55.750 --> 04:58.950
- Of course. We're
on the same team.

04:58.950 --> 05:02.050
- Except... you're
the star player

05:02.120 --> 05:04.150
and I'm the fourth line grinder
about to be sent down.

05:04.150 --> 05:06.420
- No. You're not
gonna get fired.

05:06.490 --> 05:09.060
- If I lose this
Bordoxx opportunity...

05:09.130 --> 05:11.490
- Well, that's not gonna happen.
There's no creditable data

05:11.490 --> 05:13.460
- to support this injunction.
- That's not what

05:13.530 --> 05:16.560
- Crawford and Associates claim.
- Headed up by none other

05:16.630 --> 05:18.500
than Billy Crawford...

05:18.570 --> 05:21.100
who used to mow our lawn.

05:21.170 --> 05:23.370
- I can't believe
you're from Millwood.

05:23.440 --> 05:25.770
- Yeah. That's
why my dad is sending you.

05:25.840 --> 05:28.540
[chuckling]
You are going to block

05:28.610 --> 05:31.850
this injunction, Alan,
and then our friends at Bordoxx

05:31.910 --> 05:34.320
- will be so impressed...
- That they will jump

05:34.320 --> 05:36.320
- to the CTS ship.
- Mm-hmm.

05:36.390 --> 05:39.050
They spent 25 million

05:39.120 --> 05:41.960
on legal alone last year.
70% of that

05:42.020 --> 05:44.490
went across the street
to Franklin Rose.

05:44.560 --> 05:46.990
If we can scoop
that revenue stream...

05:47.060 --> 05:49.330
neither of us will
have a thing to worry about.

05:51.830 --> 05:54.170
OK. Let's go over it again.

05:54.240 --> 05:56.140
- OK.

05:56.210 --> 05:58.270
There is no link
to these symptoms

05:58.340 --> 06:00.240
in Sodium Chloride
or Polysorbate.

06:00.310 --> 06:02.240
- So, proving even proximate
causation would be like

06:02.310 --> 06:04.180
trying to prove
the existence of God

06:04.250 --> 06:06.210
at an atheist barbecue.

06:06.220 --> 06:08.480
Besides, there's
more at stake here.

06:08.550 --> 06:11.290
If this injunction is upheld...

06:13.160 --> 06:15.360
- We will be looking at...

06:15.430 --> 06:17.890
- Opening up the doors
to anti-vaxxers.

06:17.960 --> 06:20.160
TB. Polio.

06:20.160 --> 06:22.100
All vaccinations will be

06:22.170 --> 06:24.330
on the bargaining table,
open for litigation.

06:24.400 --> 06:27.330
This would set
a catastrophic precedent

06:27.400 --> 06:30.640
that anti-vaxxers,
with their faulty science

06:30.710 --> 06:33.240
and myopic navel-gazing,
can transport us

06:33.310 --> 06:36.480
back to the Middle Ages.
We cannot let that happen.

06:36.550 --> 06:39.550
The work you do is too important

06:39.620 --> 06:42.320
and we, here at CTS,

06:42.380 --> 06:45.190
want to help you protect that.

06:45.250 --> 06:47.420
- Wow.

06:47.490 --> 06:49.990
OK. So, you'll just say all that
to the judge?

06:50.060 --> 06:53.730
- Trust me.
It will be far better.

06:53.730 --> 06:56.700
- Joanna...

06:56.770 --> 06:58.530
Franklin Rose is our
primary counsel. You know that.

06:58.600 --> 07:00.840
- Rumour has it
that you're not entirely

07:00.900 --> 07:02.940
happy with them.

07:03.010 --> 07:05.010
- Where'd you hear that?

07:05.070 --> 07:06.940
- It doesn't matter.

07:07.010 --> 07:08.740
What matters is
that you're here,

07:08.810 --> 07:11.710
which means there
is some validity to the claim.

07:11.780 --> 07:15.020
We think you'd be much happier
with us in top position.

07:20.820 --> 07:22.790
- Go to Millwood, give that

07:22.860 --> 07:24.890
rousing speech you just gave
and block this injunction.

07:24.960 --> 07:27.960
- Then we'll talk again.
- Actually Roy,

07:28.030 --> 07:29.860
I'm sending Alan to Millwood.
Joanna and I

07:29.930 --> 07:31.800
have too much history there.

07:31.870 --> 07:35.240
- No. I want her to go.
No offense.

07:35.240 --> 07:37.240
- No. Of course.

07:37.310 --> 07:39.970
- That's not going to be
a problem, is it? David?

07:40.040 --> 07:42.040
- No. Not at all.

07:42.110 --> 07:43.910
- Good. Then it's settled.

07:43.980 --> 07:45.780
Joanna goes to Millwood.

07:45.780 --> 07:48.350
- And in return you'll
take this to your team,

07:48.350 --> 07:51.290
- discuss making us top dog?
- She doesn't quit, this one.

07:53.290 --> 07:55.460
Deal. In the meantime,

07:55.460 --> 07:58.130
nobody saw me here.

08:04.130 --> 08:06.300
- No filter, no conscience.

08:06.370 --> 08:08.270
God made you the perfect lawyer.

08:08.270 --> 08:10.070
- I had a good role-model.

08:10.140 --> 08:12.740
- Right, Dad?
- You're gonna outshine me

08:12.810 --> 08:14.610
by a mile.

08:14.680 --> 08:16.740
You were amazing, sweetheart.

08:16.810 --> 08:18.610
- Thanks.

08:18.620 --> 08:20.610
I did talk myself

08:20.680 --> 08:22.480
into a ticket
to Millwood, though.

08:22.490 --> 08:23.850
- No, that's not gonna happen.

08:23.850 --> 08:25.850
I'll call Roy and I'll
convince him to send Alan.

08:25.920 --> 08:27.790
- No, it's OK. I'll go.
It's what the client wants.

08:27.860 --> 08:30.220
- Yes, but the client can
always be persuaded otherwise.

08:30.290 --> 08:33.490
- I need you here.
- It'll only be a couple days.

08:33.500 --> 08:36.100
[chuckling]

08:36.100 --> 08:38.100
- I wish I could clone you!

08:38.169 --> 08:41.100
And have one of you
in every major city that we

08:41.169 --> 08:43.100
do business in.

08:43.169 --> 08:45.370
We're really lucky
to have you here.

08:47.240 --> 08:49.110
- I didn't really have
much of a choice, did I?

08:49.180 --> 08:51.450
- What are you talking about?
Every firm in the city

08:51.450 --> 08:53.850
- wanted you.
- Yeah... but you made

08:53.920 --> 08:57.480
a pretty compelling pitch.
What'd you say?

08:57.550 --> 08:59.720
"Your dad and grandad
had a general store.

08:59.720 --> 09:01.720
We'll have a law firm."

09:05.090 --> 09:07.660
- Look, I'm not... I'm not
sending you to Millwood.

09:07.730 --> 09:09.830
- I was born there, remember?

09:09.900 --> 09:11.830
- I know what it's like.
- Yeah, and there's a reason

09:11.900 --> 09:14.170
that we left when you were
a kid. And it's gotten worse.

09:14.240 --> 09:16.400
- I'll keep my head down,
avoid any bar fights

09:16.470 --> 09:18.970
and I will get this done.

09:19.040 --> 09:21.510
Scooping Bordoxx would be

09:21.580 --> 09:23.380
huge for us.

09:25.450 --> 09:27.480
Let me do this for you.

09:29.950 --> 09:31.920
- OK. Crush them and get

09:31.990 --> 09:33.820
the hell back here. I love you.

09:33.890 --> 09:35.890
- I love you too, Dad.

09:40.760 --> 09:42.730
[sighing]

09:42.730 --> 09:45.870
[rock music]

09:45.930 --> 09:47.870
