♪♪♪

11:01.640 --> 11:03.740
[bird chirping]

11:06.050 --> 11:07.980
[sighing]

11:10.550 --> 11:12.490
[sighing]

11:19.390 --> 11:21.330
[sighing]

11:24.200 --> 11:26.670
- Hi. My name's Joanna Hanley.
- I'd like to make an appointment

11:26.740 --> 11:29.570
with Dr. Harper.
Yeah, today if possible.

11:29.640 --> 11:33.010
Uh... no, that's too late.

11:33.010 --> 11:36.540
11? I can make it.
See you in 10.

11:46.960 --> 11:49.820
- Your last check up with me
was October 2000.

11:49.830 --> 11:52.690
- I've been busy.
- How's your dad?

11:52.700 --> 11:55.300
- Good, you know,
he's still practising.

11:55.360 --> 11:57.360
- Great lawyer.
Better doubles partner.

11:57.430 --> 11:59.470
- Still is.

11:59.540 --> 12:01.970
- [air pumping]
- And your mom?

12:01.970 --> 12:04.240
- We lost touch a few years ago.

12:10.210 --> 12:12.150
- Your blood pressure is high.

12:12.210 --> 12:14.120
Have you been under a lot
of stress lately?

12:14.180 --> 12:16.850
- No, no. I'm fine.

12:16.920 --> 12:19.850
I heard that there are a few
girls in town who are sick...

12:19.860 --> 12:22.920
- Yeah, well, I can't
talk about other patients.

12:24.830 --> 12:27.460
- What proof is there linking
the vaccine to the symptoms

12:27.530 --> 12:29.330
in your professional
opinion, Doctor?

12:29.400 --> 12:32.330
- I'd like to do
some blood work.

12:32.400 --> 12:35.540
- I just need some more
information on these girls.

12:35.600 --> 12:38.510
- And I told you
that's privileged.

12:38.570 --> 12:40.510
- OK.

12:43.780 --> 12:45.710
I'm considering the HPV vaccine.

12:45.780 --> 12:48.220
As my family doctor,
you are under

12:48.280 --> 12:50.150
a professional obligation
to provide me

12:50.150 --> 12:52.550
with any and all evidence
linking the vaccine

12:52.620 --> 12:55.420
to potential side effects.

13:05.870 --> 13:08.170
[fast-paced music]

13:08.170 --> 13:10.300
♪♪♪

13:18.010 --> 13:20.250
- Can I help you?

13:20.320 --> 13:23.450
- Diane.
- Joanna?

13:23.520 --> 13:25.990
- The last time I saw you,
we were in high school...

13:26.050 --> 13:28.090
and you're still here?

13:28.160 --> 13:32.130
- Yeah. Voted most likely
to be a divorced mother of two.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.960
I'm the guidance counselor.

13:36.030 --> 13:38.130
So, uh, what about you?

13:38.200 --> 13:40.130
It's like you were
abducted by aliens.

13:40.200 --> 13:43.670
- Nope. Um, I just... moved.

13:43.740 --> 13:45.670
My dad got a job.

13:45.740 --> 13:47.840
- You married?

13:49.880 --> 13:51.950
- No.
- Lucky.

13:54.050 --> 13:56.220
So, um, are you here
to represent the girls?

13:56.220 --> 13:59.320
- I... I thought
that Billy Crawford

13:59.390 --> 14:01.620
was representing the girls?

14:01.690 --> 14:04.120
- No. He just tried to stop the
clinic so no one else gets sick.

14:04.190 --> 14:07.690
Honestly...

14:07.700 --> 14:09.930
I've never seen
anything like it.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.170
No motor control,

14:12.230 --> 14:15.300
loss of balance, tics.

14:17.640 --> 14:19.970
It started just after
the vaccine clinic.

14:20.040 --> 14:23.480
That's the brutal part.
I was spearheading it,

14:23.550 --> 14:25.710
trying to convince
the anti-vaxxers,

14:25.720 --> 14:27.720
the lesbians and the Catholics
they all needed it.

14:27.780 --> 14:31.450
The lesbians think HPV
is a "hetero thing."

14:31.450 --> 14:33.290
The Catholics won't admit
they're having sex, and don't

14:33.360 --> 14:35.220
get me started
on the anti-vaxxers.

14:35.290 --> 14:38.160
Walking, please.

14:40.600 --> 14:42.330
- This... this plaque,

14:42.400 --> 14:44.130
it used to say
"The Hanley Library".

14:44.200 --> 14:47.200
- Yeah. They renamed it
after you left...

14:47.270 --> 14:49.670
but when you prove
it's the vaccine that did this,

14:49.740 --> 14:51.640
maybe they'll
re-rename it after you.

14:51.710 --> 14:54.980
- No, I... I can't
prove that. No one can.

14:57.050 --> 15:01.250
It's just... the evidence
doesn't fully support the claim.

15:03.290 --> 15:05.420
- I'm sorry. Which side
are you on?

15:05.420 --> 15:07.350
- Don't make this personal.

15:07.420 --> 15:09.560
- Our girls are sick, Joanna.

15:09.630 --> 15:12.160
It's already personal.

15:15.430 --> 15:18.230
Why don't you leave?

15:18.300 --> 15:20.270
[tense music]

15:20.340 --> 15:22.270
♪♪♪

15:32.110 --> 15:33.910
- Your Honour.

15:33.920 --> 15:36.580
I'm here to intervene
in the petition

15:36.650 --> 15:38.850
to have my client's
vaccine clinic shut down.

15:38.850 --> 15:41.590
Joanna Hanley,
attorney for Bordoxx.

15:43.460 --> 15:46.860
- William Crawford.
Crawford and Associates.

15:49.270 --> 15:51.630
We went to school together.

15:51.700 --> 15:54.130
- Congratulations. Proceed.

15:54.140 --> 15:56.570
- Your Honour,
I filed the injunction

15:56.640 --> 15:58.940
to stop the upcoming
HPV vaccine clinic.

15:58.940 --> 16:01.240
- Your Honour, an injunction
before a full hearing

16:01.310 --> 16:03.110
on the merits would
cause my client

16:03.180 --> 16:06.380
- significant reputational harm.
- There are serious questions

16:06.380 --> 16:08.220
about the safety
of this vaccine.

16:08.220 --> 16:11.090
The court cannot allow it to be
administered to more children.

16:11.150 --> 16:13.550
- There is no proof
that Bordoxx's vaccine

16:13.560 --> 16:15.920
caused whatever
mysterious illness

16:15.990 --> 16:17.760
is happening in Millwood.

16:17.760 --> 16:19.690
- We hope to secure the opinion
of medical experts

16:19.760 --> 16:22.160
- who will testify otherwise.
- This is

16:22.160 --> 16:24.430
the actual medical opinion

16:24.430 --> 16:26.230
of the doctor of all
of the sick girls.

16:26.240 --> 16:29.070
- Medical records
are privileged.

16:32.240 --> 16:34.580
- That was given to me

16:34.640 --> 16:37.040
by my family doctor in
the course of my own treatment.

16:37.110 --> 16:41.750
Any evidentiary privilege
belongs to me, and I waive it.

16:41.820 --> 16:43.650
- Your Honour, I, um...

16:43.720 --> 16:45.720
I have here a study that would

16:45.720 --> 16:47.890
suggest a potential association

16:47.960 --> 16:50.120
between the accumulation
of neurotoxins in vaccines

16:50.130 --> 16:53.330
and, uh, neurological disorders.

16:53.400 --> 16:56.400
- If these kids can't
access the HPV vaccine,

16:56.470 --> 16:58.330
they are at serious risk
for cervical cancer.

16:58.330 --> 17:00.870
We ask the court

17:00.940 --> 17:02.870
to deny the injunction.

17:02.940 --> 17:05.140
Let the clinic go ahead.

17:05.210 --> 17:07.270
Let these students
make their own

17:07.339 --> 17:09.440
informed decision
about the vaccine.

17:14.849 --> 17:17.420
- Mr. Crawford,
your injunction is denied

17:17.490 --> 17:19.319
until such time as you

17:19.390 --> 17:21.089
can present direct evidence

17:21.160 --> 17:23.520
that links the vaccine
and the harm.

17:23.589 --> 17:25.630
Ms. Hanley,

17:25.690 --> 17:29.230
notice the your motion to stop
the injunction has been upheld

17:29.300 --> 17:31.230
by this court.

17:34.070 --> 17:37.040
[tense music]

17:37.110 --> 17:39.070
♪♪♪

17:48.850 --> 17:51.020
- [Joanna]: Thank you,
Your Honour.

17:53.060 --> 17:55.060
- Your client's gonna pay.

17:55.060 --> 17:57.760
- Yeah? We'll see about that.

17:57.830 --> 18:00.030
Thank you.

18:03.500 --> 18:06.430
- I'm so sorry, Ben.
- You did your best.

18:08.500 --> 18:11.840
- Hi.
- Thanks, Mr. Crawford.

18:11.910 --> 18:14.040
♪♪♪

18:24.450 --> 18:26.350
- Hi.
- [Hey!]

18:26.360 --> 18:29.360
- I stopped the injunction
for Bordoxx.

18:29.360 --> 18:31.530
- Joanna, that's amazing!
I knew you would do it.

18:31.590 --> 18:34.430
- [Well, court went pretty much
as we planned.]

18:34.430 --> 18:37.900
You would've done the same
thing. This was our case.

18:37.970 --> 18:39.900
- The client will be
over the moon! Prepare for

18:39.970 --> 18:41.900
- the ship jumping.
- [Let's not pop]

18:41.900 --> 18:43.900
[the champagne yet.]
- Congratulations.

18:43.970 --> 18:45.710
- [Thank you.
It was a team effort.]

18:45.770 --> 18:47.840
- So...

18:47.910 --> 18:49.840
how is it, being home?

18:49.910 --> 18:52.850
- I don't know. It's weird.

18:52.920 --> 18:55.220
Um...

18:55.280 --> 18:57.780
I need you to draft
settlement agreements

18:57.850 --> 19:00.020
as quickly as possible
for the three families.

19:00.090 --> 19:03.390
- I'll get you the names.
- OK. I'm on it.

19:07.030 --> 19:08.800
- I saw it today, Alan.

19:08.800 --> 19:11.500
This could be a lot worse
than we thought.

19:11.570 --> 19:13.700
- The twitching?
- [Yes.]

19:13.770 --> 19:15.800
[The lawyer hasn't signed]

19:15.870 --> 19:18.670
an agreement yet, so we need
to move as quickly as possible.

19:18.740 --> 19:20.610
- And then...

19:20.680 --> 19:23.740
- And "and then" what? We win.

19:23.810 --> 19:25.980
- And then we celebrate.

19:26.050 --> 19:28.620
- Yeah, of course.

19:30.520 --> 19:33.450
Uh... get me
those agreements, OK?

19:33.520 --> 19:35.290
- You got it.

19:41.960 --> 19:44.830
[birds chirping]
- [Joanna]: <i> This offer to settle</i>

19:44.830 --> 19:46.730
all current and future claims

19:46.800 --> 19:48.670
is not an admission of fault
by Bordoxx Industries.

19:50.840 --> 19:53.270
Their vaccine
has been rigorously tested

19:53.340 --> 19:56.440
and has met all
government safety standards.

19:56.510 --> 19:59.450
However...

19:59.510 --> 20:01.310
as a show of good faith

20:01.380 --> 20:03.880
and to aid in your care,

20:03.950 --> 20:05.850
my client is willing

20:05.850 --> 20:07.990
to offer $50000.

20:08.060 --> 20:11.520
It could be
in your account today.

20:11.590 --> 20:13.530
- Shouldn't our lawyer
look at this?

20:13.530 --> 20:16.600
- You could do that, but...

20:16.670 --> 20:18.900
he would just slow down
the process.

20:18.970 --> 20:21.530
And he would take
one-third of the money

20:21.540 --> 20:23.670
for doing nothing.

20:23.740 --> 20:26.210
- He told me about that part.

20:26.280 --> 20:29.110
- It's better if that money goes
into your own pocket, I think.

20:35.750 --> 20:37.480
We only want you to get better.

20:37.550 --> 20:39.490
[sombre music]

20:39.550 --> 20:41.490
♪♪♪

20:51.030 --> 20:53.270
♪♪♪

21:04.650 --> 21:06.710
♪♪♪

21:13.520 --> 21:15.520
- You can't do this.
They're my clients.

21:15.590 --> 21:17.360
- Did you sign
a retainer agreement?

21:19.260 --> 21:22.360
- Then they aren't.
- Implied lawyer-client

21:22.430 --> 21:24.400
relationship can exist
even in the absence

21:24.470 --> 21:26.270
of a formal agreement:
the Devaux case.

21:26.270 --> 21:28.270
- By the time you go
to court to prove it,

21:28.340 --> 21:30.170
I'm going to have settled
with all of them

21:30.240 --> 21:31.400
and be back on a plane.

21:31.410 --> 21:32.770
- 17 years later

21:32.780 --> 21:34.610
you still need to be
the smartest person in the room.

21:34.680 --> 21:37.580
- I don't need to be.
It just works out like that.

21:37.650 --> 21:39.480
- You are robbing them.

21:39.480 --> 21:42.750
- This is a fair settlement.
- These girls deserve millions.

21:42.820 --> 21:44.920
- They're not gonna
get that, Billy.

21:44.990 --> 21:47.950
You can't win this.

21:47.960 --> 21:50.220
We'll bury you in documents.
We'll file

21:50.290 --> 21:53.960
endless procedural motions.
Litigation is war.

21:53.960 --> 21:56.100
- Oh...

21:56.160 --> 21:58.670
- We'd destroy you. Billy.

22:02.200 --> 22:05.170
You'd have to be crazy or stupid
to take this case.

22:05.170 --> 22:08.140
- You know you're
the bad guy, right?

22:21.460 --> 22:23.590
- Well, you picked a good time
to come by for supper.

22:23.590 --> 22:27.330
The Matheson Meatball
is known far and wide.

22:27.400 --> 22:29.260
- Really?
- No.

22:29.330 --> 22:32.070
Sharon's, uh...

22:32.070 --> 22:34.070
at bridge once a week,

22:34.140 --> 22:36.540
so spaghetti's about
all I can handle.

22:36.610 --> 22:39.670
I hear you want to settle.

22:39.740 --> 22:42.780
Millwood's a small town.

22:42.840 --> 22:46.010
- My client is willing
to offer $50 000

22:46.080 --> 22:48.480
to settle all current
and future claims

22:48.550 --> 22:51.020
against Bordoxx,
its subsidiaries and assigns.

22:51.090 --> 22:53.320
- I'm not settling.

22:56.630 --> 22:58.630
- You may want to think
about what's best

22:58.690 --> 23:00.630
for your daughter.

23:07.700 --> 23:09.700
- I have a good job.

23:09.770 --> 23:12.110
My kid gets good health care.

23:12.170 --> 23:14.610
I don't need your money.

23:17.110 --> 23:19.580
- You can always use more.

23:19.650 --> 23:21.450
- Can you?

23:21.520 --> 23:23.480
Sometimes I think

23:23.550 --> 23:25.320
people have too much.

23:25.390 --> 23:28.560
- If you go to court,

23:28.620 --> 23:30.560
you may get nothing.

23:37.130 --> 23:39.670
100 000.

23:44.340 --> 23:46.270
[sighing]

23:46.280 --> 23:48.480
- My wife...

23:48.540 --> 23:51.610
is a wreck,

23:51.610 --> 23:53.650
and my little girl...

23:57.920 --> 23:59.950
It's the toughest thing
in the world,

23:59.960 --> 24:01.990
watching your kid
trying to be brave.

24:10.770 --> 24:13.000
You can let yourself out.

24:23.880 --> 24:25.810
- Hi.

24:29.180 --> 24:32.050
I was just talking
with your father.

24:32.050 --> 24:34.920
- One of the girls just called
me. I know what you're doing.

24:34.990 --> 24:36.790
- Our vaccine has been

24:36.860 --> 24:39.130
thoroughly tested.

24:39.130 --> 24:41.130
The offer is just

24:41.200 --> 24:43.330
our way of saying that we
hope you get better.

24:43.400 --> 24:45.230
- This started after I
got the vaccine.

24:45.300 --> 24:48.000
- That doesn't mean
that the vaccine caused it.

24:48.000 --> 24:51.140
Temporal precedence
is a necessary

24:51.210 --> 24:53.740
but not sufficient
condition of causation.

24:53.740 --> 24:56.610
- You know, I was
considering law.

24:56.680 --> 24:58.750
I've always gotten As,

24:58.810 --> 25:02.480
but... I have
final exams coming up.

25:02.550 --> 25:05.350
I study...

25:05.420 --> 25:08.360
I just can't remember things.

25:08.420 --> 25:10.960
My brain is all foggy.

25:10.960 --> 25:13.430
I had to...

25:13.490 --> 25:15.300
I had to quit cheerleading.

25:15.360 --> 25:18.000
This wasn't how I
pictured turning 18.

25:20.040 --> 25:22.800
- You're already 18?
- My birthday...

25:22.870 --> 25:25.200
was last week.

25:25.270 --> 25:28.170
- Do you, uh, want
some money for yourself?

25:28.240 --> 25:31.750
Just for you. Your dad doesn't
even have to know about it.

25:35.820 --> 25:38.350
How does $50 000 sound?

25:42.720 --> 25:44.720
- That sounds really good.

25:58.310 --> 26:00.810
[pen clicking]

26:04.610 --> 26:06.750
[sombre music]

26:06.820 --> 26:08.780
♪♪♪

26:13.160 --> 26:15.760
♪♪♪

26:24.630 --> 26:28.070
- Are you proud of yourself?

26:30.570 --> 26:32.570
- I'm not the enemy, Diane.

26:32.570 --> 26:34.570
- Oh, no?

26:34.640 --> 26:36.410
Who are you, then?

26:43.620 --> 26:45.520
You must be happy
with your work.

26:45.590 --> 26:47.650
- At least they're
getting something.

26:47.720 --> 26:49.660
- But, if your vaccine didn't

26:49.720 --> 26:51.490
cause the symptoms, why are
you giving away money?

26:51.560 --> 26:53.560
- The truth?

26:53.630 --> 26:55.400
- Couldn't hurt.

26:55.460 --> 26:57.260
- To avoid bad press.

26:57.270 --> 26:59.600
[sighing] It's a lot of money

26:59.600 --> 27:01.800
for people around here,
but for my client,

27:01.870 --> 27:05.000
- it's a rounding error.
- "A rounding error"?

27:05.070 --> 27:08.540
Wow. - You wanted the truth.

27:10.810 --> 27:12.680
- You know...

27:12.680 --> 27:15.750
one minute we're making plans
to go to a bush party.

27:15.820 --> 27:17.850
Next thing I know, you're gone.

27:17.920 --> 27:20.190
And I don't hear from you

27:20.250 --> 27:22.790
in 15 years...

27:26.030 --> 27:28.900
- 17... actually.

27:32.370 --> 27:35.200
- Then you ride into town
to screw us.

27:35.270 --> 27:37.540
Lot of nerve.

27:39.610 --> 27:41.340
- I should've called.

27:45.050 --> 27:47.050
- I should get this mutt home.

27:47.120 --> 27:49.820
- Hey, is there somewhere
I can eat around here?

27:49.820 --> 27:51.820
- Where they won't
poison your food? Hmm...

27:53.920 --> 27:56.260
Lucy's.

27:56.320 --> 27:58.260
- Um...

27:58.330 --> 28:00.260
do you wanna join me?

28:02.260 --> 28:04.360
- I can't. Derek's dropping
the kids off soon.

28:04.430 --> 28:06.330
- Oh.

28:06.400 --> 28:08.530
- Rain cheque...

28:08.540 --> 28:12.170
on dinner. - Sure thing.

28:14.210 --> 28:16.180
- Come on!

28:19.750 --> 28:23.080
♪♪♪

28:28.260 --> 28:32.130
♪♪♪

28:37.300 --> 28:39.200
♪♪♪

28:51.980 --> 28:54.480
- Oh! I am so sorry.

28:54.550 --> 28:57.720
I'm not normally this clumsy.

28:57.790 --> 28:59.650
- Oh, no. It's OK.

28:59.720 --> 29:01.490
I've had a long day too.

29:04.460 --> 29:06.390
How's the spinach salad?

29:06.460 --> 29:08.730
All right.

29:08.730 --> 29:11.260
A cheeseburger and fries, then.

29:11.330 --> 29:14.270
- Somebody die?

29:17.070 --> 29:19.070
- Uh, no. I'm a lawyer.

29:19.070 --> 29:23.210
- Nobody's perfect.
- The, um, vaccine lawyer?

29:23.280 --> 29:25.210
- Yeah.

29:25.280 --> 29:27.480
- So you're settling
with all the girls?

29:27.550 --> 29:30.250
- I'm just doing my job.
- Yeah.

29:30.250 --> 29:33.350
I just... wish everyone
was looking

29:33.420 --> 29:35.320
for a fix instead of someone
to blame it on, you know?

29:37.360 --> 29:39.290
But I guess that's just not
how the world works, huh?

29:39.290 --> 29:41.660
I'll get you that burger.

29:44.570 --> 29:46.830
[objects clattering] [gasping]

29:46.900 --> 29:48.700
- [Luna]: Oh, my God.

29:48.700 --> 29:51.500
Hey, hey. Let me help.

29:55.280 --> 29:57.010
- I'm OK. Ah!
- MOLLY!

29:57.080 --> 29:59.380
- Oh, my God!
- Please! Molly!

29:59.380 --> 30:02.220
You're gonna be OK!
You're gonna be OK!

30:02.280 --> 30:04.250
Come on! Molly!

30:04.320 --> 30:07.850
Molly!

30:07.920 --> 30:09.720
Molly, it's OK! It's OK!

30:09.790 --> 30:12.190
[rising music]

30:12.260 --> 30:14.330
♪♪♪

30:24.210 --> 30:26.240
- Yeah. I mean,
one second she was fine

30:26.310 --> 30:28.510
and then she just went down.

30:28.580 --> 30:30.740
I travelled with her in the
ambulance, but I don't know.

30:30.810 --> 30:33.180
No one will tell me anything
'cause I'm not family.

30:35.220 --> 30:37.380
No, I'm OK.

30:37.450 --> 30:39.220
I should go.

30:39.220 --> 30:41.190
I'll call you later. Promise.

30:48.260 --> 30:50.160
I've got some change.

30:50.230 --> 30:52.770
- I don't want your money.

30:55.040 --> 30:57.040
- How is she?

30:57.100 --> 30:59.040
- A lot better.

31:02.010 --> 31:04.010
- Here.

31:05.910 --> 31:07.780
She's never had
a seizure before?

31:07.850 --> 31:09.980
- Never.

31:17.390 --> 31:19.460
- But she had started
showing symptoms?

31:19.460 --> 31:22.060
- She made me promise
not to tell anyone.

31:22.130 --> 31:24.200
- Luna... if the number

31:24.270 --> 31:26.200
of cases are growing
and our vaccine

31:26.200 --> 31:28.600
- actually caused this, then...
- It didn't.

31:28.670 --> 31:30.900
- What?

31:30.970 --> 31:33.710
- I said "it didn't".

31:36.680 --> 31:39.080
[knocking] [machine beeping]

31:39.150 --> 31:41.480
- Hi. I'm Joanna.

31:41.550 --> 31:43.980
- Joanna rode with me here
in the ambulance.

31:44.050 --> 31:46.250
- Oh. I'm Wendy,

31:46.320 --> 31:48.250
Molly's mom. Thanks for
taking care of her.

31:48.320 --> 31:50.320
- Of course.

31:53.290 --> 31:55.230
Molly, Luna just told me...

31:55.300 --> 31:58.900
you didn't get the HPV vaccine.

32:04.370 --> 32:07.770
- We've only ever
been with each other, so...

32:07.780 --> 32:11.080
I figured I didn't need it.

32:11.080 --> 32:13.580
- Molly!

32:13.650 --> 32:15.550
- Uncle Billy!
- Hey.

32:15.620 --> 32:17.450
What happened?

32:17.520 --> 32:20.020
- She had a seizure.
- You OK?

32:20.090 --> 32:22.090
- Yeah.

32:22.160 --> 32:24.290
You should see the other guy.

32:26.730 --> 32:28.700
- What are you doing here?

32:33.330 --> 32:35.230
- Your niece never
got the vaccine.

32:35.300 --> 32:37.340
- What? She told Wendy
that she did.

32:37.410 --> 32:40.140
- She didn't want you guys
to find out she was gay.

32:40.210 --> 32:42.880
- Oh, God. We've known forever.

32:42.880 --> 32:45.210
We were just...
waiting for her to tell us.

32:47.110 --> 32:49.080
- So, now what?
- Now? Now, I go home

32:49.150 --> 32:51.020
and get a big fat
slap on the back.

32:51.090 --> 32:53.150
This absolves my client.

32:55.190 --> 32:58.490
- All right.
So, I guess that's it.

33:01.230 --> 33:03.230
- Not for you.

33:03.300 --> 33:05.160
Something else is making
these girls sick. You have

33:05.230 --> 33:07.170
to figure out what it is.

33:07.240 --> 33:09.200
[sighing] Just start with things

33:09.270 --> 33:11.900
they all do, have and use:

33:11.970 --> 33:15.110
shampoos, activities, cleaning
products at their school,

33:15.180 --> 33:17.310
places they like to shop,
local hangouts.

33:17.380 --> 33:19.310
- Look, I don't
have the resources.

33:19.380 --> 33:22.050
- You're Crawford
and Associates.

33:22.120 --> 33:24.220
- Associates just
sounded cooler.

33:24.290 --> 33:26.850
Yeah.

33:26.860 --> 33:29.290
One-man band.

33:33.290 --> 33:35.460
- OK. So, my retainer

33:35.530 --> 33:37.930
is normally 10K, but...

33:38.000 --> 33:41.270
buy me a burger,
I'm yours for an hour.

33:41.340 --> 33:43.240
- Well, that's better

33:43.300 --> 33:45.240
than nothing, I guess.

33:45.310 --> 33:47.840
To The Boot.

33:47.910 --> 33:50.710
[rock music]

33:50.780 --> 33:52.580
♪♪♪

33:56.520 --> 33:58.480
- Is there a wine list?
- Oh, yeah.

33:58.490 --> 34:00.890
I have it memorized:
red and white.

34:00.960 --> 34:03.090
Can we get two beers?

34:05.260 --> 34:07.560
- How's the calamari?
- Oh, it's good.

34:07.630 --> 34:09.560
It's like the onion rings,
but... squid.

34:09.630 --> 34:12.300
So...

34:12.300 --> 34:14.770
15-year-old girl got sent home
from Calculus today

34:14.840 --> 34:17.040
- for disrupting class.
- Another one.

34:18.909 --> 34:21.639
It isn't a lawsuit yet.
It's just a fishing expedition.

34:21.710 --> 34:24.110
Without a cause,
you don't have a case.

34:24.179 --> 34:26.110
- Thank you.

34:26.179 --> 34:28.750
Where would you start?

34:28.820 --> 34:31.650
- You've gotta start at the
beginning. Who's patient zero?

34:31.650 --> 34:33.449
- Taylor Matheson, we think.

34:33.460 --> 34:35.920
- And... it's only
affecting girls.

34:35.989 --> 34:37.860
- So far.

34:37.929 --> 34:40.260
- Well, you can probably
rule out a disease,

34:40.260 --> 34:43.400
which is good because there's
no one to sue,

34:43.400 --> 34:45.630
and no one to pay
your legal fees.

34:50.270 --> 34:52.270
Molly seems like a good kid.

34:52.270 --> 34:56.409
- Yeah, she's
a definite over-achiever.

34:56.409 --> 34:58.540
Kind of kid you know is gonna

34:58.610 --> 35:00.310
leave town and do
something great.

35:02.550 --> 35:05.350
[phone ringing]

35:05.420 --> 35:07.350
I gotta get this. It's Wendy.

35:07.420 --> 35:09.360
- Yeah, of course.
- [Billy]: Hey!

35:16.200 --> 35:18.100
- You're David Hanley's
daughter?

35:18.170 --> 35:20.770
- Yeah. Ah!

35:20.830 --> 35:22.770
[patrons gasping and laughing]

35:22.840 --> 35:25.300
[woman laughing]

35:25.370 --> 35:27.640
- Are you OK?

35:27.640 --> 35:31.010
What the hell was that?

35:31.080 --> 35:33.050
- I have no idea.

35:45.860 --> 35:47.830
[bird chirping]

35:52.130 --> 35:54.070
Is it swelling?

35:54.130 --> 35:56.740
- It's not... not swelling.

35:56.740 --> 36:00.070
- I can't go back
to work like this.

36:00.140 --> 36:02.170
- Well, you should stay.

36:02.240 --> 36:04.740
You know, just 'til
the swelling goes down.

36:04.750 --> 36:06.780
- We're a corporate firm.

36:06.850 --> 36:08.680
We work on important cases.

36:08.750 --> 36:11.020
- This is an important case
around here.

36:13.150 --> 36:15.320
- That's not what I meant.

36:17.630 --> 36:19.630
[Billy sighing]

36:19.690 --> 36:23.200
Did you just come back here
right after school?

36:26.370 --> 36:28.230
- Pretty much.

36:28.300 --> 36:31.640
- Surely business would have
been better somewhere else.

36:31.640 --> 36:33.640
- Yeah.

36:33.710 --> 36:36.880
But that "somewhere else"
wouldn't have been my home.

36:39.110 --> 36:41.350
- So, you stay
because of nostalgia?

36:41.420 --> 36:43.650
- No.

36:43.720 --> 36:45.890
No, it's not that. It's...

36:48.760 --> 36:50.920
The feeling I get
driving up the 59

36:50.990 --> 36:53.160
on my way back
from somewhere, it's...

36:55.700 --> 36:57.630
It's tough to explain.

37:00.600 --> 37:03.200
- OK. Really, how does it look?

37:03.270 --> 37:06.040
- Well, you look like
you're from Millwood.

37:08.340 --> 37:11.740
- It was nice seeing you again,
Billy. Good luck.

37:11.810 --> 37:13.750
- Yeah.

37:13.810 --> 37:15.710
You take care
of yourself, Counselor.

37:15.780 --> 37:17.820
[soft music]

37:17.890 --> 37:19.690
♪♪♪

37:21.760 --> 37:23.820
[engine starting]

37:32.630 --> 37:34.500
- [I absolved Bordoxx.]

37:34.500 --> 37:36.370
- Well, hello to you too.

37:36.440 --> 37:38.240
- [Sorry.]

37:38.240 --> 37:41.370
- It's been a long day.
- [So...]

37:41.380 --> 37:43.780
does that mean the client
doesn't have to pay out?

37:43.840 --> 37:46.580
- Not a cent.
Completely off the hook.

37:46.580 --> 37:48.580
- [Joanna!]

37:48.650 --> 37:50.450
That's great! I mean,
that's a better result

37:50.450 --> 37:53.220
than anyone could've expected.
Are you celebrating?

37:53.290 --> 37:56.190
- I had a glass of wine,

37:56.260 --> 37:58.990
took a bath, shaved my legs

37:59.060 --> 38:01.160
I did everything I could
think of doing.

38:01.230 --> 38:04.460
It's a small town.

38:04.470 --> 38:07.330
- You OK? You don't sound
like you just won a huge case.

38:07.400 --> 38:10.040
- [sighing]
- I don't know.

38:12.670 --> 38:15.140
You ever think...

38:15.210 --> 38:17.380
- [What?]

38:20.010 --> 38:22.620
- It's just we've worked so hard
to get here. Did you ever

38:22.680 --> 38:24.480
think it would feel different?

38:24.550 --> 38:27.220
- You got anything smaller
on your mind, Counselor?

38:27.290 --> 38:31.090
- Yeah. Sorry.

38:31.090 --> 38:33.160
- Have you told your dad?

38:33.160 --> 38:36.630
- No. Not yet.

38:36.700 --> 38:39.130
- Hmm. I thought he'd be your
first call.

38:39.200 --> 38:42.670
- Yeah...

38:42.740 --> 38:46.170
- Sure you're OK?

38:46.240 --> 38:49.440
- Of course.
I'll see you tomorrow.

38:49.510 --> 38:51.640
- Congratulations, Counselor.

38:53.480 --> 38:55.510
[soft music]

38:55.520 --> 38:57.620
♪♪♪

39:06.590 --> 39:08.590
[sighing]

39:24.780 --> 39:26.550
- All right, ma'am?

39:26.550 --> 39:28.550
- Oh, yeah.

39:28.620 --> 39:30.180
I... I used to live
in this house.

39:30.250 --> 39:33.050
- Your father's David Hanley?

39:34.960 --> 39:37.520
Didn't think a Hanley would ever
set foot in this town again.

39:43.860 --> 39:46.800
♪♪♪

39:58.210 --> 40:01.380
- Taylor. Is everything
all right?

40:01.450 --> 40:04.480
- Well, my parents are fighting
over your settlement offer.

40:07.890 --> 40:11.190
- Ahem. There... there is no
settlement offer to fight over.

40:11.260 --> 40:13.530
Now that we can prove

40:13.590 --> 40:15.490
that the vaccine
isn't responsible,

40:15.560 --> 40:17.700
Bordoxx has no reason
to pay out.

40:22.870 --> 40:25.040
- Bordoxx is a corporation.

40:25.110 --> 40:27.270
They don't care about me.

40:27.340 --> 40:30.280
But you came to my house
and you sat with me!

40:30.280 --> 40:32.180
I knew you were on
the other side, but I thought,

40:32.180 --> 40:34.350
"At least she's a person."

40:34.350 --> 40:37.780
I was wrong. You're not.

40:40.090 --> 40:42.720
- I want you to get better.

40:48.600 --> 40:51.530
- Taylor...
- I have lost everything!

40:51.600 --> 40:53.930
My life is ruined.

40:56.170 --> 40:58.300
I have no idea
what is wrong with me

40:58.370 --> 41:00.370
or... or why.

41:00.440 --> 41:02.570
- Now that you know that
the vaccine didn't do this,

41:02.640 --> 41:04.910
you can find out the real cause.

41:04.980 --> 41:07.210
- Don't pretend like
you're on my side.

41:07.280 --> 41:10.350
You're a hot shot lawyer.
You could help me if you wanted.

41:10.420 --> 41:14.450
- That's not really what I do.

41:14.460 --> 41:16.260
- No, of course not.

41:16.320 --> 41:18.290
Your job is to...

41:18.360 --> 41:20.260
screw people over.

41:20.330 --> 41:22.460
Good, hardworking people.

41:24.470 --> 41:27.130
And you saw me and you thought,
"Well, she's just a sick kid.

41:27.200 --> 41:29.640
She'll agree to anything."

41:31.710 --> 41:33.640
How can you live with yourself?!

41:42.550 --> 41:44.920
My dad wanted me to be a lawyer.

41:44.990 --> 41:47.490
But after what I've seen today,

41:47.490 --> 41:50.620
I'm never turning into you.

42:04.240 --> 42:07.640
♪♪♪

